	<pb facs="liv_002041_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
<lb/><opener><space extent="2" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="small"><unclear cert="medium">Res.</unclear> David Livingstone <add place="below">L L D.</add></add>
<lb/><dateline><space extent="1" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement type="town">Hamilton</settlement></placeName> <date when="1864-08-08">8<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Aug</abbr><expan>August</expan></choice><!-- Placement? --> 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/>1864</date></dateline><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="underline sup">r</hi> Baines</persName></salute></opener>
<lb/><p>I feel very much
<lb/>flattered by your
<lb/>invitation to lecture
<lb/>before the <orgName><placeName><settlement type="city">Leeds</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>Philosophical &amp;
<lb/>literary society</orgName> and
<lb/>I think I could tell
<lb/>my story among
<lb/><orgName><placeName><region>Yorkshire</region></placeName> men</orgName> with
<lb/>as little embarrassment 
<lb/>as among <term type="people">Scotchmen</term>
<lb/>but I am anxious

	<pb facs="liv_002041_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>to get back to <placeName><bloc>Africa</bloc></placeName>
<lb/>again and by some
<lb/>work North of the 
<lb/><term type="nationality"><term type="people">Portuguese</term></term> prevent
<lb/>my past labours
<lb/>from being rendered
<lb/>fruitless by those
<lb/>inveterate <term type="occupation"><orgName>slavers</orgName></term> -
<lb/>I left my steamer
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="city">Bombay</settlement></placeName> for
<lb/>this very object
<lb/>when I might have
<lb/>sold her - and now
<lb/>in order to have a 
<lb/>few months quiet
<lb/>but not of idleness
<lb/>refuse all public

	<pb facs="liv_002041_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>engagements except
<lb/>the <orgName>British association</orgName>
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="town">Bath</settlement></placeName> - </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Please do accept
<lb/>hearty thanks for
<lb/>your kind offers
<lb/>of hospitality
<lb/>and present a
<lb/>warm greeting
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="underline">rs</hi> Baines</persName></p>
<lb/><closer><salute>from Yours Ever</salute><!-- Change as appropriate -->
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer><!-- Change as appropriate --> 

<lb/><postscript><p>I think I have
<lb/>an invitation from
<lb/>

	<pb facs="liv_002041_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>the <term type="occupation">secretary</term> and hope
<lb/>that this which I 
<lb/>could not answer
<lb/>sooner will suffice
<lb/>for an answer
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><persName><choice><abbr>D.L.</abbr><expan>David Livingstone</expan></choice></persName></p></postscript>

            </div>
